Web Ontology Language
OWL semantics
In OWL there is no Unique Name Assumption (UNA)
The fact that two entities have different URIs does not imply 
that they are different entities
We have to explicitly assert, if we want to, that two entities are 
different from each other 
In the (Semantic) Web, different resources talk about the same 
entity
